<h2><a name="hor">Horizontally banded variant</a></h2>
<p>
<a HREF="../images/a/af-1928.gif">
<img SRC="../images/a/af-1928.gif" alt="[Afghanistan June or Sep.1928-Jan.1929, variant]" HEIGHT=216 width=384 border=0></a> 
image located by <i>Markus Wiehler</i>, 15 August 2010</p>

<p>&nbsp;Wikipedia has this flag:
<a href="http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flag_of_Afghanistan_July_1928-September_1928.svg">
http://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Flag_of_Afghanistan_July_1928-September_1928.svg</a>. 
I asked the uploader about his source, because I did not find the image nor here 
nor at other vexillological websites. The uploader, Fornax, sent me an eMail 
with two cards from the Flag Research Institute. In fact, it seems to be an 
important one, because it introduced the colors black-red-green.<br><i>Markus 
Wiehler</i>, 15 August 2010</p>

